text: Rowan Reda Araby or Rowan Elaraby (born 29 July 2000 in Alexandria) is an Egyptian professional squash player. As of February 2018, she was ranked number 36 in the world. Araby is the 2017 World Junior Champion beating Egyptian compatriot, Hania El Hammamy. The previous year, 2016, Araby lost in the final to Nouran Gohar. == See also == * Official Women's Squash World Ranking ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Egyptian female squash players
